<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-05-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-05-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="473" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d473">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Hirsch</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-05-13"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 13,
                            1890</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 87.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 118 of the 25th
                        ultimo, in further reference to the alleged robbery, about 1 year ago, of
                        the American missionaries Rev. Mr. McDowell and Dr. Wishard by three
                        Nestorian mountaineers, whose names are given in your note to the Sublime
                        Porte of the 24th ultimo.</p>
                    <p>A speedy and just disposition of this complaint seems very desirable.</p>
                    <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">James G. Blaine.</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>